articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy awarded two Polish volunteers state awards during a stopover on Saturday, but did not meet any officials as relations between the two countries are strained over grain imports.
articles.title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy stops over in Poland to award two volunteers

articles.author: Felix Light
articles.description: The ethnic Armenian leadership of breakaway Nagorno-Karabakh said on Saturday that the terms of their ceasefire with Azerbaijan were being implemented, with work proceeding on the delivery of humanitarian aid and evacuation of the wounded.
articles.title: Karabakh Armenians say ceasefire being implemented, aid is arriving

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: British interior minister Suella Braverman will raise the "the unsustainable pressures" created by illegal migration when she makes a three-day visit to the U.S. this week, her office said on Sunday.
articles.title: Suella Braverman, UK interior minister, to raise 'unsustainable' migration pressures during U.S. visit

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un has vowed to promote cooperative relations with China in a letter to President Xi Jinping, the North's state media KCNA reported on Sunday.
articles.title: Kim Jong Un tells Xi Jinping in letter he hopes to promote cooperation

articles.author: Francis Kokoroko
articles.description: Hundreds of demonstrators gathered in the Ghanaian capital Accra on Saturday for a third day of anti-government protests linked to economic hardship that have led to dozens of arrests.
articles.title: Multi-day protests over economic crisis grip Ghana's capital

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 35 people were killed in southeastern Benin on Saturday after a fire broke out at a shop where witnesses said gasoline was being unloaded, a justice ministry representative said.
articles.title: Fire in shop kills 35 people in southeastern Benin

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanon's army said it fired tear gas at Israeli forces over the border on Saturday in response to smoke bombs fired at its troops, though Israel said Lebanon started the confrontation.
articles.title: Lebanese army says it exchanged tear gas, smoke bomb fire with Israel

articles.author: Anna Voitenko
articles.description: The use of heavy weapons supplied by the West in the fierce battle raging on the outskirts of Bakhmut, which was captured by Russia in May, is inflicting a significant toll on enemy lines, Ukrainian commanders have told Reuters.
articles.title: Ukrainian heavy artillery inflicts 'hell' on Russian lines near Bakhmut

articles.description: Follow on Apple, Google or Spotify. Listen on the Reuters app. Read the episode transcript.
articles.title: How the killing of a Sikh plumber in Canada led to a diplomatic war with India

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Even China's population of 1.4 billion would not be enough to fill all the empty apartments littered across the country, a former official said on Saturday, in a rare public critique of the country's crisis-hit property market.
articles.title: Even China's 1.4 billion population can't fill all its vacant homes, former official says
